==Russian==
===Letter===
{{infl|ru|letter|lower case||upper case|А}}

# The first letter of the Russian [[Cyrillic]] alphabet. It is followed by the letter [[б]] (''b'').

====Usage notes====
The Russian name for '''а''' (''a'') is '''а''' (''ā''), and in stressed syllables it has the sound of the long '''a''' in ''f'''a'''ther''. In unstressed positions, it is pronounced as a [[schwa]], like the '''o''' in ''m'''o'''ther''. (Unstressed Russian '''а''' (''a'') is pronounced the same as unstressed Russian '''о''' (''o'').)

===Conjunction===
{{infl|ru|conjunction}}

# [[but]], [[and]] (introduces a new or different meaning).
#:[[Сегодня]] [[теплый|тепло]], а [[вчера]] [[быть|было]] [[холодный|холодно]]. (''Segodnja teplo, a včera bylo xolodno.'') — “It is warm today, but yesterday it was cold.”
#:[[Это]] [[не]] [[яблоко]], а [[груша]]. (''Eto nje jabloko, a gruša.'') — “This is not an apple, but a pear.”
#:А [[что]]? (''A što?'') — “Why so?”
#:а [[тот|то]] (''a to'') — “or else”

